<p>Something like this?</p>
<p><code><br />
exec("gpio -g mode 4 out");<br />
$state = $_GET["total"];</p>
<p>if ($state == "on"){<br />
   exec("gpio -g write 4 1")<br />
sleep(1);<br />
  exec("gpio -g write 4 1")<br />
}<br />
</code></p>
<p>I will make a mobile web page with one button that turns on a relay for a second (or maybe less, I have to find out how long it needs to be on, currently I just know that it doesn&#8217;t do nothing if it is switched on very quick) and then turns it off. With this, it opens/closes/stops the door depending on the current state.</p>
