                </header>

                <!-- display the comment text -->
                <div class='comment_text entry-content-wrapper clearfix'  itemprop="commentText" >
                <p>Hi Marco,</p>
<p>No need to put this post on your web, just a little information.</p>
<p>I think I have discovered why my relays are in the high state when rebooting, acordin to this link:<br />
<a href="http://www.raspberrypi.org/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?f=44&#038;t=35321" rel="nofollow">http://www.raspberrypi.org/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?f=44&#038;t=35321</a></p>
<p>There is chenges in the state of the pins of the Pi, from the dirrent revision, and &#8220;of course&#8221; I had decided to use some of the pins, with the high state after reboot.</p>
<p>Also, a little input to your great guide, maybe add PPTP (easy, but not that secure) ot OpenVPN to the PI, so that using this remote control from the web, can be done using a VPN tunnel instead of having a website wiith full access to the entire world. </p>
<p>Best reagrds</p>
<p>Lars</p>
